description: myFC Holding AB engages in the research and development of renewable energy for powering portable electronics. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm. The company went IPO on 2014-05-27. The firm's technology generates green energy via hydrogen to recharge and supplement batteries. myFC's basic design includes small, flat and scalable fuel cells, which are mainly used in electrified consumer applications and electric vehicles. The firm is a spin-off by the KTH Royal Institute of Technology.
naicsSubsector: Electrical Equipment, Appliance, and Component Manufacturing
